Package com.smartnsoft.droid4me.analytics

Useful when it comes to handle analytics reporting in an industrial way.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AnalyticsLogger
    Enables to mark that an entity needs to log some analytics when being used.
    AnalyticsLogger.AnalyticsDictionaryLogger<DictionaryType>
    An analytics logger which states the tag and a dictionary of the analytics event to report.
    AnalyticsLogger.AnalyticsTagLogger
    An analytics logger which states the tag of the analytics event to report.
    AnalyticsSender<DictionaryType>
    A very basic abstraction of an agent which is able to send analytics.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    IssueReporter
    A utility class which enables to report issues resulting from Throwable occurrences.
    IssueReporter.OutOfMemoryErrorEntry
    An entry regarding an OutOfMemoryError occurrence.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    AnalyticsLogger.AnalyticsDisabledLoggerAnnotation
    An annotation which enables to express that an entity, usually an Activity or a Fragment, does not wish to report any analytics usage.
    AnalyticsLogger.AnalyticsEnabledLoggerAnnotation
    An annotation which enables to express that an entity, usually an Activity or a Fragment, wishes to report analytics usage.
    AnalyticsLogger.AnalyticsTagLoggerAnnotation
    An annotation which enables to express that an entity, usually an Activity or a Fragment, wants to report analytics usage.

Package com.smartnsoft.droid4me.analytics Description

Useful when it comes to handle analytics reporting in an industrial way. This package is not yet stable, and changes may result from further architecture changes.
